NHDPlusV2 Attribute Subset

Source: R/get_vaa.R
get_vaa.Rd

Return requested NHDPlusv2 Attributes

get_vaa(atts = NULL, path = get_vaa_path(), download = TRUE)

Arguments

atts

character The variable names you would like, always includes comid
path

character path where the file should be saved. Default is a persistent system cache as retrieved by user_cache_dir. Also see: get_vaa_path
download

logical if TRUE, the default, will download VAA table if not found at path.

Value

data.frame

Details

The VAA data is a aggregate table of information from the NHDPlusV2 elevslope.dbf(s), PlusFlowlineVAA.dbf(s); and NHDFlowlines. All data originates from the EPA NHDPlus Homepage here. To see the location of cached data on your machine use get_vaa_path. To view aggregate data and documentation, see here

Examples

get_vaa,NHDPlusV2 Attribute Subset,NHDPlusV2 Attribute Subset — get_vaa,Source: R/get_vaa.R,get_vaa.Rd,character(0),get_vaa,character(0),list(title = "Description", contents = "
Return requested NHDPlusv2 Attributes
"),list(image = list(src = "https://usgs-r.github.io/nhdplusTools/logo.png"), description = "Return requested NHDPlusv2 Attributes"),get_vaa(atts = NULL, path = get_vaa_path(), download = TRUE),list(list(name = "atts", description = "
character The variable names you would like, always includes comid
"), list(name = "path", description = "
character path where the file should be saved. Default is a\npersistent system cache as retrieved by user_cache_dir.\nAlso see: get_vaa_path
"), list(name = "download", description = "
logical if TRUE, the default, will download VAA table if not\nfound at path.
")),TRUE,
# \donttest{
get_vaa("slope")
